'''Guangzhou International Light Festival''' (or '''GZ Light''') ({{lang-zh|'''廣州國際燈光節'''}}) is a light exhibiting festival held annually along the [[Pearl River (China)|Pearl River]] in the city of [[Guangzhou]], [[China]].<ref>[http://news.sina.com.cn/o/2015-10-09/doc-ifxirmqz9641006.shtml 新征途 广州国 际灯光节被评为国 际光年特别推荐活动] 新浪 （2015-10-09）</ref><ref>[http://news.21cn.com/hot/social/a/2015/1113/15/30268531.shtml 广州国际灯光节被评为国际光年特别推荐活动] 21CN （2015-11-13）</ref><ref>[http://www.light2015.org/Home/Event-Programme.html Event Programme] 2015 International Year of Light And Light-Based Technologies</ref> The festival occurs every November since 2010, when the [[2010 Asian Games|16th Asian Games]] left many lighting facilities on the ground of the event.
