{{Infobox recurring event |name = Houston Dragon Boat Festival |logo = |image = |caption = |location = [[Buffalo Bayou]], [[Houston, Texas]] |years_active = 2001-present |dates = first weekend of May |genre = [[dragon boat]] racing |website = http://www.texasdragonboat.com }}
The '''Houston Dragon Boat Festival''' is held in [[Houston, Texas]]. The Houston Dragon Boat Festival is a race down [[Buffalo Bayou]], using decorated canoes called "[[dragon boat]]s".
==History== The first festival was held in October 2001 at [[Allen's Landing]] in downtown Houston.<ref>{{cite news |first=Nancy |last=Sarnoff |title=Beware of floating dragons on the bayou |url=http://houston.bizjournals.com/houston/stories/2001/10/15/tidbits.html?page=2 |work=Houston Business Journal |date=2001-10-15 }}</ref> In 2004, the festival added a second event – the Gulf Coast International Dragon Boat Regatta held in October at Clear Lake Park. 2005 saw the festival host the U.S. Central Region Championships in conjunction with the Gulf Coast International regatta.<ref>{{cite news |title=A Year of Corporate Philanthropy: October 2005 |url=http://houston.bizjournals.com/houston/stories/2005/11/14/focus20.html|work=Houston Business Journal |date=2005-11-11 |quote=Wal-Mart was presenting sponsor of the second annual Gulf Coast International Dragon Boat Regatta at Clear Lake Park, which helps increase awareness of Asian and Asian-American culture. }}</ref>
== Boathouse == The Texas Dragon Association plans to build the first [[boathouse]] along the downtown Bayou for non-motor boat craft. The Houston Endowment donated $75,000 to build the boathouse at 501 N. York Street.<ref>{{cite news |title=Buffalo Bayou to get boathouse |url=http://houston.bizjournals.com/houston/stories/2007/01/15/daily15.html |work=Houston Business Journal |date=2007-01-16 }}</ref>
