'''Mercedes-Benz Fashion Week Miami''' is an annual [[fashion week]] held in [[Miami, Florida]], [[United States]]. [[Mercedes-Benz Fashion Week]] Miami, not to be confused with [[Miami Fashion Week]], is held every year during the Summer at the Raleigh Hotel at 1775 Collins Avenue in [[South Beach]], [[Miami Beach]]. Mercedes-Benz Fashion Week Miami works together with [[New York Fashion Week]], and is the country's largest, and most important fashion week for swimwear.  [[IMG (company)|IMG]] whom first brought its runway event to South Beach in 2004, had an ongoing partnership with Mercedes-Benz.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Mercedes Benz Fashion Week Swim 2015|url = http://www.jamessantiagophotography.com/mercedes-benz-fashion-week-swim/|website = Fashion Photography|publisher = |accessdate = 2015-12-11}}</ref>  However, due to changes in ownership, as IMG was acquired by [[William Morris Endeavor]] and [[Silver Lake Partners]] in a $2.2 billion deal,<ref>{{Cite web|title = UPDATE: WME Brass Welcome IMG Staffers As Acquisition Deal Closes|url = http://www.deadline.com/2013/12/wme-silver-lake-acquire-img-worldwide/|website = Deadline|accessdate = 2015-12-11|language = en-US}}</ref> the agency lost Mercedes-Benz as a title sponsor.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://fashionista.com/2015/05/img-swim-week-miami-postponed|title = Miami's Fashion Week Swim Is Going on Hiatus|date = May 11, 2015|accessdate = |website = Fashionista.com|publisher = |last = Klein|first = Alyssa Vingan}}</ref>  The show was cancelled for 2015 but will resume in 2016 after re-branding the popular event.

