{{Infobox Magazine | title = Renaissance Magazine | image_file =Renaissance Magazine.gif | image_size = 150px | image_caption = | editor = Adam Eyler & Tanya Laird | editor_title = | frequency = Bi-monthly | circulation = 35,000 | category = | company = Lionheart Entertainment LLC | publisher = | founded = 1996 | firstdate = | country = United States | based = Houston, Texas | language = [[English language|English]] | website = [http://www.renaissancemagazine.com] | issn = 1088-906X }} '''''Renaissance Magazine''''' is a glossy [[United States|American]] magazine published bimonthly. Each issue comprises approximately 90 pages, and includes articles about the contemporary [[renaissance faire]] experience, medieval and renaissance history, castles, heraldry, cooking, and interviews with key individuals in the renaissance fair industry. It was founded in 1996 by "Lady Kimberly," a graduate of [[Yale University]], and has its headquarters in [[Bridgeport, Connecticut]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Renaissance Magazine|url=http://us-ct.bizdirlib.com/m/node/31445|work=Connecticut Business Database|accessdate=15 November 2015}}</ref> The magazine is owned by Lionheart Entertainment LLC in Houston, Texas.
The magazine is the sponsor of the Annual Renaissance Festival Awards together with ''Celtic Music'' magazine.<ref>{{cite news|title=Winners of the 7th Annual Renaissance Festival Awards of 2011|url=http://renaissancefestivalmusic.com/2012/7th-annual-renaissance-festival-awards-of-2011/|accessdate=15 November 2015|work=Renaissance Festival Podcast|date=1 March 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117021531/http://renaissancefestivalmusic.com/2012/7th-annual-renaissance-festival-awards-of-2011/|archivedate=17 November 2015|df=}}</ref>
