{{Infobox Newspaper | name = The Patriot on Sunday | logo = | image = | caption = | type = Sundays newspaper | format = | owners = [[Mpho Balopi]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mmegi.bw/index.php?sid=1&aid=144&dir=2012/October/Friday5/|title=Mmegi Online :: The Patriot is born|work=Mmegi Online|access-date=2017-10-15}}</ref> | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = 2012 | political = | language = | ceased publication = | headquarters = | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = }}
'''''The Patriot on Sunday''''' is a Botswana newspaper published on Sundays. The Newspaper was founded in 2012 and in part owned by parlimantarian by [[Mpho Balopi]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mmegi.bw/index.php?sid=1&aid=144&dir=2012/October/Friday5/|title=Mmegi Online :: The Patriot is born|work=Mmegi Online|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref> The newspaper is indexed in [[AllAfrica.com]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/list/aans/post/af/cat/botswana/pubkey/publisher:editorial:00011654.html|title=Botswana -- The Patriot, Gaborone|website=allAfrica.com|language=en|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref> The Newspaper was involved in a Freedom of the Press dispute with [[Printing and Publishing Company Botswana]] because of a negative perspective on the ruling party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://freedomhouse.org/report/freedom-press/2014/botswana|title=Botswana {{!}} Country report {{!}} Freedom of the Press {{!}} 2014|website=freedomhouse.org|language=en|access-date=2017-06-06}}</ref>
